{
  "texts": [
    "In this paper, we begin the investigation of stochastic optimal control problems for large interacting particle systems of stochastic evolution equations in Hilbert spaces.",
    "More precisely, in a real, separable Hilbert space H, for n ≥ 1 we consider x(s) = (x 1 (s),.",
    ", x n (s)) ∈ H n to be the solution of the system of H-valued stochastic differential equations (SDEs) (1.1) dx i (s) = [Ax i (s) + f (x i (s), µ x(s), a i (s))]ds + σ(x i (s), µ x(s))dW (s), s ∈ [t, T ] x i (t) = x i ∈ H, i = 1,.",
    ", n, where A: D(A) ⊂ H → H is a linear densely defined maximal dissipative operator, µ x(s):= 1 n n i=1 δ x i (s) is the empirical measure of x(s), and W (s) is a cylindrical Wiener process in some Hilbert space Ξ acting as a common noise.",
    "The precise conditions on the admissible controls a i (•) and the coefficient functions will be given in Sections 3, 4."
  ]
}